oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Surveying a waterway
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Odell Powell shown in south channel of W type waterway. Distance from one channel to the other is twenty seven feet. Depth of channel, one foot. Waterway was shaped and seeded during August. Fescue, ladino clover, and alsike was seeded.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s
